# MIIRF Fund Data API

**Mahaana IGI Islamic Retirement Fund (MIIRF)** data is loaded automatically from the production fund-data API. For future work on MIIRF, treat this API as the single source of truth.

## API

- **URL:** `https://fdepprodmahaana-gkb9bdeehudhdedy.z02.azurefd.net/marketfeedinvestmentuniverse/api/fund-data?name=miirf`
- **Origin header:** `https://www.mahaana.com` (required so the API accepts requests)

## Implementation

- **Config:** `src/lib/miirf-fund-api.ts`
  - Base URL: `FUND_DATA_API_BASE` (env `NEXT_PUBLIC_FUND_DATA_API_BASE_URL` or the URL above)
  - Full path: `/marketfeedinvestmentuniverse/api/fund-data?name=miirf`
  - Request origin: `MIIRF_API_ORIGIN = "https://www.mahaana.com"`
- **Usage:** MIIRF page fetches via `getMiirfFundDataForPage()` and passes `fundData?.overview`, `fundData?.performance`, `fundData?.subfunds` to MIIRFOverviewSection, MIIRFPerformanceSection, and MIIRFSubfundsSection. Overview, main fund performance (five risk profiles), and subfunds (Money Market, Debt, Equity) all come from this API when available.
- **Daily updates:** The MIIRF page uses `revalidate = 86400` (24 hours) so Next.js runs the fund-data API at least once per day when the cache expires. Values (NAV, performance, subfund data, etc.) update automatically; no manual content updates are required.

When adding or changing MIIRF features, use the API response shape (e.g. `miirf`, `miirfmmsf`, `miirfdsf`, `miirfesf` with `info`, `price`, `perf`, `holdings`, `asset_alloc`) and keep the existing fetch + transform pattern in `miirf-fund-api.ts`.
